<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 758.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 687, of the 19th instant,
                            regarding the reported release of three German prisoners of war who were
                            detained on Ceylon, has been received. The matter is commended to your
                            attention.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>